A sentence must have:
✅ Subject (who/what the sentence is about)
✅ Verb (action/state of being)
✅ Object (receives the action, optional)

Examples:
Simple Sentence (S + V + O): She (S) eats (V) an apple (O).
Compound Sentence (using conjunctions): I like tea, but she prefers coffee.
Complex Sentence: Although it was raining, we went outside.
